      "writtenOn": "2021-06-29T20:14:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This used to be one of the designed features of the driver. However, after a close examination of QEMU with libusb, I found it was not needed at all. libusb with WinUsb does not rely on these QUERY ID ioctls to reach the device instance. libusb can get a handle to the device without any issue with the device\u0027s original VID/PID. So these QEURY ID ioctls are simply used here to fool Windows Device Manager to load WinUsb driver. Beyond this, no more changes are made to your original CL.",
